entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/ArchaeopterTransvector:Victory#0
entry.value: Enemy signatures no longer detected. Returning to cycle.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/CyberneticaDatasmith:Idle#0
entry.value: The flesh is weak, the machine is strong.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/CyberneticaDatasmith:Idle#1
entry.value: In binary, rhythm and song. I would that you could hear.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/CyberneticaDatasmith:Idle#2
entry.value: There can be no improvement on the Omnissiah's design.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/CyberneticaDatasmith:Idle#3
entry.value: In nomine imperii et mechanici et spiritus omnissiah.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/FulguriteElectroPriest:Broken#0
entry.value: Nostra potex decit… our will fails!

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/IronstriderBallistarius:Victory#0
entry.value: For 10,000 years, our victory has been certain.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/KataphronDestroyer:Broken#0
entry.value: Only Men Fear. We Once Were-

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/KnightCrusader:Attack#0
entry.value: We are but a weapon in the right hand of the Emperor.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/KnightCrusader:Attack#1
entry.value: For the honour of the Questor Mechanicus!

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/KnightCrusader:Idle#1
entry.value: For the jousts of my homeworld.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/KnightCrusader:Idle#2
entry.value: My house is famed for its humility, you know.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/KnightCrusader:Victory#0
entry.value: It is no shame to fall at my hand.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/TechPriestManipulus:Broken#0
entry.value: Logic dictates this is not happening.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/TechPriestManipulus:Hurt#0
entry.value: We… we did not plan for this.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/TechPriestManipulus:Idle#0
entry.value: Oh, I am just leaking power.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/SkitariiMarshal:Idle#3
entry.value: Servo Skull, I name thee Morte.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/SkitariiVanguard:Attack#1
entry.value: Let's see who the Radium kills faster…

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/SkitariiVanguard:Idle#0
entry.value: I've 99 upgrades, but rad-protection isn't one of them.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/SkitariiVanguard:Idle#3
entry.value: I mean, I wouldn't eat near us either.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/SkitariiVanguard:Shaken#0
entry.value: Magos, we are dying for you.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/SkitariiVanguard:Victory#0
entry.value: Not even a half-life left of them.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/TechPriestDominus:Idle#3
entry.value: Yes… I see their moves and countermoves.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/TechPriestDominus:Victory#0
entry.value: I planned this victory several moves ago. But the sweetness remains.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/Headquarters:Attack#1
entry.value: Their lives are for us to take, not you.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/Headquarters:Hurt#0
entry.value: We are sustaining civilian casualties. Acceptable.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/Headquarters:Idle#1
entry.value: Clones are being sent to the Protoservitor Cradles.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/Headquarters:Idle#2
entry.value: In the name of the Omnissiah, hab-fanes cleared.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/Headquarters:Shaken#0
entry.value: The masses are terrified. Provosts have been deployed.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/Headquarters:Victory#0
entry.value: External threats eliminated. Turning attention to dissent.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:AlliedFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: Space Marines sighted, commander. Comms channels are open.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:AlliedUnit:AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar#0
entry.value: Lord Commissar spotted. Preparing to drive him closer.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:AlliedUnit:AstraMilitarum/TankCommander#0
entry.value: Sir, glad to see an officer who appreciates the value of armour, sir!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:Cover#0
entry.value: Not sure how, but the tank is in cover, sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:EnemyFaction:Necrons#0
entry.value: Xenos sighted, sir. Preparing to show them what a real metal monster is.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:EnemyFaction:Orks#0
entry.value: Greenskins in the area, sir. They're not going to make a Skullhamma out of us!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:EnemyFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: Enemy Adeptus Astartes located. No Fellblades in sight.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:EnemyUnit:Neutral/Enslaver#0
entry.value: Sir, advise rapid retreat. We can't guarantee this vehicle won't be compromised.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:Hurt#0
entry.value: Severe damage sustained, sir. Advise return to Mars for repairs.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:Idle#1
entry.value: Checking all eleven barrels for hell, sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:Idle#2
entry.value: The enemy is weak, sir. We will help them fail.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:Idle#4
entry.value: When I grow up, I want to be a Hellhammer. Sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:Idle#5
entry.value: Did you hear that Vance Stubbs lost a hundred Baneblades, sir? Somewhat careless.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:QuestStory0#0
entry.value: Ready to reclaim Gladius Prime, sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:QuestStory2#0
entry.value: Sir, will all respect, that Tech-Priest isn't fit to oil our sponsons.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:QuestStory3#0
entry.value: We'll leave the underground exploration to the infantry. Sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:QuestStory4#0
entry.value: We can keep the Xenos back, not a problem, sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:QuestStory5#0
entry.value: Kastelans! We'll need all eleven barrels, sir!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:Shaken#0
entry.value: No retreat, sir! Not sure this thing actually goes backwards, anyway.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:Victory#0
entry.value: Target eliminated, sir. Reloading all barrels.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Baneblade:WireWeed#0
entry.value: Sir, advise we move the vehicle; the crew can't handle this wire.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:AlliedFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: Allied Astartes sighted, praise the Emperor

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:AlliedUnit:AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar#0
entry.value: Commissar sighted. Glad he's on the frontlines… far away from us.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:Artefact#0
entry.value: Shells aren't scratching that thing. What's it made of?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:Artefact#1
entry.value: We'll be purged just for looking at that.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:Attack#3
entry.value: Target under fire. Glad we're back here!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:Cover#0
entry.value: Perfect artillery location. They won't see us coming.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:EnemyFaction:AstraMilitarum#0
entry.value: We always have a gift for traitors—132mm of the Emperor's fury.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:EnemyFaction:Necrons#0
entry.value: Tin men? 15km seems the perfect distance to engage them.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:EnemyFaction:Orks#0
entry.value: Ah, Greenskins. What this cannon was built for.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:EnemyFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: Renegade Marines? I wonder if their haloes protect them against hi-ex?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:EnemyUnit:Neutral/Enslaver#0
entry.value: What are those THINGS? Keep them at range, men.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:Hurt#0
entry.value: Crew compartment penetrated… it's a mess in here.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:Idle#0
entry.value: Did you hear about the Saint of Basilisks? He got canonized. Geddit?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:Idle#1
entry.value: Don't send a Manticore to do a Basilisk's job.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:Idle#2
entry.value: I pity the poor grunts on the frontlines… but not enough to join 'em.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:Idle#3
entry.value: Just tell us when there's something to shoot.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:Idle#4
entry.value: Nothing happens in war… and it happens repeatedly.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:Shaken#0
entry.value: Is someone actually shooting… at us?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:Victory#0
entry.value: Turning enemies into craters for ten millenium, sah!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Basilisk:WireWeed#0
entry.value: Biowire? I mean there are worse firing positions, like inside the Great Rift…

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Bullgryn:EnemyFaction:AstraMilitarum#0
entry.value: Wait, oos fighting fer the Emperor? Us or dem?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Bullgryn:EnemyFaction:Orks#0
entry.value: Orks. Tough, good lookin, clevver. Like us.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Bullgryn:EnemyFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: Da Emperor's kids? We goota fight dem?!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Bullgryn:EnemyUnit:Neutral/Enslaver#0
entry.value: Nah, I don't get what dey are.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Bullgryn:Idle#1
entry.value: One Ogryn on dead Ork's chest. Uh… two! Two Ogryns…

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Bullgryn:Idle#3
entry.value: We do what's we's told. And you told us nuffin.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:AlliedFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: Praise the Emperor, the Astartes are here!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:AlliedUnit:AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar#0
entry.value: Chests out, bellies in lads, it's the Lord Commissar.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Attack#0
entry.value: Can anyone see what we're shooting at?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Attack#1
entry.value: Enemies in front, commissar at our back…

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Attack#4
entry.value: Pour on the las-fire, we might just make it.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Broken#0
entry.value: I didn't sign up for this!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Broken#1
entry.value: Run lads, and hope the Commissar ain't watching!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Broken#2
entry.value: They're killing us! And we can't kill them back!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Broken#3
entry.value: This is a bloody Death World!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Broken#4
entry.value: Where are the reinforcements? Where are-!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Cover#0
entry.value: Back in the trenches, thank the Emperor.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:EnemyUnit:Neutral/Psychneuein#0
entry.value: Big bugs from Prospero—keep them away from the psykers!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Idle#3
entry.value: It's the silence before the battle that's the worst.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Idle#4
entry.value: Just playing games, sir, Commissar says it's good for morale.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Idle#5
entry.value: Life in the guard, sir. Terribly hard.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Idle#6
entry.value: Receiving you loud and clear, sir!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:QuestStory0#0
entry.value: I still can't believe we survived. So many…

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:QuestStory1#0
entry.value: Getting the gang back together, sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:QuestStory2#0
entry.value: A new city? Are we sure—no, sir, not questioning your orders, sir!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:QuestStory3#0
entry.value: Those storms make my head hurt—will we be trapped here forever?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:QuestStory4#0
entry.value: They're inside the city! Get back!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:QuestStory5#0
entry.value: My mum always said, 'never trust a tech-priest'. She was alright, my mum.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Shaken#0
entry.value: Can we pray? Oh, Emperor, oh Guilliman, preserve us.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Shaken#3
entry.value: If we stay, the enemy will shoot us. If we run, the Commissar will shoot us!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Shaken#4
entry.value: Can we get better guns, please?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Victory#1
entry.value: Ha! I feel like we took down a Titan with a lightstick.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Victory#2
entry.value: To the memory of Cadia and to Creed…

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Guardsman:Victory#4
entry.value: Wow, the Primer is right! These xenos are easy!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Headquarters:AlliedFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: Commander, HQ has sighted the allied Space Marines.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Headquarters:AlliedUnit:AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar#0
entry.value: Happy to see you out in the field, Sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Headquarters:Artefact#0
entry.value: Xenos artefact dangerously near to the city, sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Headquarters:Cover#0
entry.value: How… is a city… in cover?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Headquarters:EnemyFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: Space Marines approaching. They'll wipe the city out if they get inside the walls.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Headquarters:Idle#2
entry.value: Who's been playing Tarot? Put it away.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Headquarters:Shaken#0
entry.value: Pulling back to defensive positions, sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Headquarters:WireWeed#0
entry.value: Was building this city on bio-wire such a great idea?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:AlliedFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: Good of the Astartes to turn up.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:AlliedUnit:AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar#0
entry.value: Where do Commissars get their lunch? At the commissary. Heh.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:Artefact#0
entry.value: If we can't shoot that thing, I'm not interested.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:Attack#0
entry.value: Can anyone see if the target's still there?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:Broken#0
entry.value: Fall back, you hounds, fall back!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:Cover#0
entry.value: Like they say on Krieg: keep your mortars in cover, and they'll cover you.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:EnemyFaction:Necrons#0
entry.value: Let's peel their metal hides off 'em.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:EnemyFaction:Orks#0
entry.value: Firing at Greenskins is a waste of ammo.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:EnemyFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: If you have to fire at a Space Marine, make sure you hit.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:EnemyUnit:Neutral/Enslaver#0
entry.value: Blow those hellspawn back to the warp!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:Hurt#0
entry.value: I ain't got time to bleed.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:Idle#0
entry.value: Do you know how long it takes to fix bayonets on lascannons?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:Idle#1
entry.value: The Xenos can come to us.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:Idle#2
entry.value: There's something waiting for us out there…

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:Idle#3
entry.value: We're just like a tank that can actually hit the target.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/HeavyWeaponsSquad:Shaken#0
entry.value: We're not meant to be under fire, Sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Hydra:AlliedUnit:AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar#0
entry.value: It is useful to have a man to keep us grounded.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Hydra:EnemyFaction:Necrons#0
entry.value: Such strange flying machines, so deadly.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Hydra:EnemyFaction:Orks#0
entry.value: Greenskin fliers are crude, but effective.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Hydra:EnemyFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: Can I shoot down Thunderhawks? Let's find out!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Hydra:EnemyUnit:Neutral/Enslaver#0
entry.value: Floating isn't flying, you alien horrors.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Hydra:Hurt#0
entry.value: We watch over the skies, you're meant to watch over us.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Hydra:Idle#3
entry.value: This planet has the most amazing sunsets. Sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/ImperialStrongpoint:AlliedFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: Strongpoint reporting Adeptus Astartes on the perimeter—friendlies.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/ImperialStrongpoint:AlliedUnit:AstraMilitarum/Baneblade#0
entry.value: Thrill to see a Baneblade, sir. Especially when the guns are pointed the other way.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/ImperialStrongpoint:Artefact#0
entry.value: Strongpoint reporting Xenos artefact in close proximity.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/ImperialStrongpoint:Broken#0
entry.value: Strongpoint is lost, repeat, Strongpoint is lost.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/ImperialStrongpoint:EnemyFaction:AstraMilitarum#0
entry.value: Strongpoint reporting traitor movement on the peripherary.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/ImperialStrongpoint:EnemyFaction:Necrons#0
entry.value: Strongpoint reporting Necrons are on the move.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/ImperialStrongpoint:EnemyFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: Strongpoint reporting… Emperor preserve us… enemy Adeptus Astartes.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/ImperialStrongpoint:Hurt#0
entry.value: Strongpoint reporting—not sure if we can survive this, sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/ImperialStrongpoint:Shaken#0
entry.value: Sir, can you hear us? We're under fire.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/ImperialStrongpoint:WireWeed#0
entry.value: Bio-wire is infesting the command center, sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LemanRussBattleTank:AlliedFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: The Marines have joined the party! Good of 'em.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LemanRussBattleTank:AlliedUnit:AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar#0
entry.value: Another noble footslogger. Why did only Yarrick get his own Baneblade?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LemanRussBattleTank:Attack#0
entry.value: Sending some lovely shells their way, sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LemanRussBattleTank:Cover#0
entry.value: In the trees, setting an ambuscade, sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LemanRussBattleTank:EnemyFaction:AstraMilitarum#0
entry.value: We'll be rolling the bones of heretics before the day is done..

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LemanRussBattleTank:EnemyFaction:Orks#0
entry.value: Prepared to self-destruct—Orks love to borrow Leman Russ tanks.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LemanRussBattleTank:EnemyFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: This cannon is designed to make Marines weep.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LemanRussBattleTank:Hurt#0
entry.value: Wow, that one went straight through the plating!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LemanRussBattleTank:Victory#0
entry.value: Another victory for the galaxy's most popular tank!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LemanRussBattleTank:WireWeed#0
entry.value: Bio-wire, the only thing more common than the Leman Russ.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar:AlliedFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: It is always welcome to see loyal Astartes… if surprising.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar:Artefact#0
entry.value: Xenos filth. We should burn it.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar:Attack#0
entry.value: Shoot them or I'll shoot you!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar:Broken#0
entry.value: I can't let the men see me like this!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar:Cover#0
entry.value: Tactically sound to hide, but not great for morale.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar:EnemyFaction:AstraMilitarum#0
entry.value: Traitors! Filth! YOU SHALL FACE THE EMPEROR'S JUSTICE!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar:EnemyFaction:Necrons#0
entry.value: Tin filth. Let's melt them down for more bullets.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar:EnemyFaction:Orks#0
entry.value: Greenskin thugs. Imperial rigour should make swift work of them.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar:EnemyFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: Renegade dregs of our Emperor's proudest creation. We must wipe them from the galaxy.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar:Idle#2
entry.value: Rations are halved. That's why I look a little Gaunt.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar:Idle#5
entry.value: Do your duty in the name of- Oh, I always forget this bit.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar:Shaken#0
entry.value: A spiritu dominatus, Domine, libra nos.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar:Victory#0
entry.value: Setting an example to my troops.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar:WireWeed#0
entry.value: It would be foolhardy to remain in the bio-wire, however brave.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/MarauderBomber:Attack#1
entry.value: If you can see 'em, we can hit 'em.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/MarauderBomber:Attack#3
entry.value: Anything under the bombsight is fair game.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/MarauderBomber:Cover#0
entry.value: If we was flying any lower, why we'd need bells on this thing.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/MarauderBomber:Hurt#0
entry.value: We got three engines out, we got more holes in us than a trader's grox, the vox-caster is gone and we're leaking fuel…

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/MarauderBomber:Idle#0
entry.value: I ain't much of a hand at makin' speeches

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/MarauderBomber:Idle#1
entry.value: I swear, Carpenter, these bombs talks back.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/MarauderBomber:Idle#2
entry.value: Does anyone know how to land this thing?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/MarauderBomber:Idle#3
entry.value: Practisin manoov-res. Like the Primer says.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/MarauderBomber:Shaken#0
entry.value: Moving to higher altitudes—flak poppin all round us.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/PrimarisPsyker:AlliedFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: I sense… great good from these.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/PrimarisPsyker:AlliedUnit:AstraMilitarum/LordCommissar#0
entry.value: A mind twisted to absolutism… fascinating.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/PrimarisPsyker:Artefact#0
entry.value: Old bones built these little toys.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/PrimarisPsyker:Attack#1
entry.value: I feel the Emperor's eyes on me.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/PrimarisPsyker:Attack#2
entry.value: I burn you in His name.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/PrimarisPsyker:Broken#0
entry.value: His light, where is His light?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/PrimarisPsyker:Cover#0
entry.value: The hidden mind is the wise mind.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/PrimarisPsyker:EnemyFaction:AstraMilitarum#0
entry.value: We are of two minds, it appears.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/PrimarisPsyker:EnemyFaction:Necrons#0
entry.value: I can feel nothing from them. Nothing.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/PrimarisPsyker:EnemyFaction:Orks#0
entry.value: A swell of-, such fierce loving emotion.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/PrimarisPsyker:EnemyFaction:SpaceMarines#0
entry.value: Such steely surety… on the surface.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/PrimarisPsyker:EnemyUnit:Neutral/Enslaver#0
entry.value: I feel its hunger, its desire for the fecundity of our mind

entry.name: Eldar/Headquarters:Idle#2
entry.value: I long to return to my craftworld, to doff this mask.

entry.name: Eldar/Headquarters:Shaken#0
entry.value: I fear death and the Great Enemy.

entry.name: Eldar/Headquarters:Victory#0
entry.value: This gate will not close, yet.

entry.name: Eldar/Guardian:Idle#1
entry.value: When we will return to the crystal halls?

entry.name: Eldar/Guardian:Idle#3
entry.value: Seer, I hope your sight is true.

entry.name: Eldar/Guardian:Victory#0
entry.value: Arrogant, to stand against the Aeldari.

entry.name: Eldar/FirePrism:Attack#3
entry.value: Weapons of the ancients, do not fail us.

entry.name: Eldar/FirePrism:Hurt#0
entry.value: This damage is of no consequence.

entry.name: Eldar/FirePrism:Idle#2
entry.value: Why must we use such weaponry?

entry.name: Eldar/FirePrism:Idle#3
entry.value: The craftworlds are so far away.

entry.name: Eldar/FireDragon:Idle#0
entry.value: Let us tell tale of firestorms and ash.

entry.name: Eldar/FireDragon:Idle#3
entry.value: There is nobility in incineration, is there not?

entry.name: Eldar/FireDragon:Victory#0
entry.value: Their face in death is… ashen.

entry.name: Eldar/CrimsonHunter:Attack#2
entry.value: From the air, we dispense… lessons.

entry.name: Eldar/CrimsonHunter:Idle#0
entry.value: I have a desire… for speed.

entry.name: Eldar/CrimsonHunter:Idle#2
entry.value: This environment is rich in targets…

entry.name: Eldar/CrimsonHunter:Idle#3
entry.value: Nothing is more deadly than arrogance in battle.

entry.name: Eldar/Autarch:Broken#0
entry.value: Retreat is a part of war.

entry.name: Eldar/Autarch:Idle#0
entry.value: Cegorach makes work for idle Autarchs.

entry.name: Eldar/Autarch:Idle#1
entry.value: I shall now recite the litany of battle…

entry.name: Eldar/Autarch:Idle#3
entry.value: There is no peace in my mind.

entry.name: Eldar/Autarch:Victory#0
entry.value: They will not try my patience again.

entry.name: Eldar/FarseerSkyrunner:Attack#0
entry.value: I shape your future… it is short.

entry.name: Eldar/FarseerSkyrunner:Attack#3
entry.value: I am the helmsman of my people.

entry.name: Eldar/FarseerSkyrunner:Idle#1
entry.value: The future is always in motion.

entry.name: Eldar/FarseerSkyrunner:Idle#2
entry.value: I see the future and shape it too.

entry.name: Eldar/FarseerSkyrunner:Idle#3
entry.value: I long for the crystal and the circuit.

entry.name: Eldar/FarseerSkyrunner:Shaken#0
entry.value: It was not meant to be this way!

entry.name: Eldar/Spiritseer:Attack#3
entry.value: I am of an ancient race!

entry.name: Eldar/Spiritseer:Broken#0
entry.value: I retreat, lest I join my charges.

entry.name: Eldar/Spiritseer:Hurt#0
entry.value: My life drains into the crystal…

entry.name: Eldar/Spiritseer:Idle#0
entry.value: The dead are in my care.

entry.name: Eldar/Spiritseer:Idle#1
entry.value: I speak to you, my departed friends.

entry.name: Eldar/Spiritseer:Idle#2
entry.value: It is quiet, in the spirit halls.

entry.name: Eldar/Spiritseer:Idle#3
entry.value: Hear the infinity circuit of the planet. It whispers!

entry.name: Eldar/Spiritseer:Shaken#0
entry.value: We are so few, left alive.

entry.name: Eldar/Spiritseer:Victory#0
entry.value: I cannot celebrate death, even a foe's.

entry.name: Eldar/AvatarOfKhaine:Attack#0
entry.value: YOU DARE BATTLE WITH WAR INCARNATE?!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Ratling:Attack#2
entry.value: If we can see it, we can hit it.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Ratling:Attack#3
entry.value: Like shooting tarcks in a pot.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Ratling:Hurt#0
entry.value: Get us out of the frontlines!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Ratling:Idle#0
entry.value: Amasec seconds? Don't mind if I do.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Ratling:Idle#1
entry.value: There's good eating on a Grox, y'know?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Ratling:Idle#2
entry.value: This? I didn't take it! Don't tell the Commissar!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Ratling:Idle#3
entry.value: Ante up and don't tell Sarge.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Ratling:Shaken#0
entry.value: Keep us safe and we'll keep you safe.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/Ratling:Victory#0
entry.value: Through the eye! I think that deserves extra rations.

entry.name: ChaosSpaceMarines/ChaosCultist:Attack#0
entry.value: In the name of the Dark Gods!

entry.name: ChaosSpaceMarines/ChaosCultist:Idle#0
entry.value: Do you ever wonder… never mind.

entry.name: ChaosSpaceMarines/ChaosCultist:Idle#3
entry.value: For the glory of the Perfect Prince.

entry.name: ChaosSpaceMarines/DarkDisciple:Broken#0
entry.value: I see into the warp, oh…

entry.name: ChaosSpaceMarines/DarkDisciple:Idle#1
entry.value: Mankind is doomed. Chaos is our salvation.

entry.name: ChaosSpaceMarines/DarkDisciple:Idle#3
entry.value: The truth of the universe is at hand!

entry.name: ChaosSpaceMarines/Headquarters:Attack#0
entry.value: They dare to come before us!

entry.name: ChaosSpaceMarines/Headquarters:Attack#2
entry.value: We will make charnel of your bones!

entry.name: ChaosSpaceMarines/Headquarters:Idle#3
entry.value: The masses will bow before us.

entry.name: ChaosSpaceMarines/Headquarters:Victory#0
entry.value: So die all who face us.

entry.name: Eldar/Warlock:Attack#1
entry.value: The flames of our fury cleanse them.

entry.name: Eldar/Warlock:Attack#3
entry.value: The mind is our greatest weapon.

entry.name: Eldar/Warlock:Idle#1
entry.value: The great enemy waits in the warp.

entry.name: Eldar/Warlock:Idle#2
entry.value: I long for the crystal blooms.

entry.name: Eldar/Warlock:Idle#3
entry.value: I miss the masques of my Craftworld.

entry.name: SpaceMarines/DevastatorCenturion:Attack#0
entry.value: Aiming for armour, Praise the Emperor.

entry.name: SpaceMarines/DevastatorCenturion:Broken#0
entry.value: Suits are holding, but we're falling back.

entry.name: SpaceMarines/DevastatorCenturion:Hurt#0
entry.value: Got through the armour… both sets.

entry.name: SpaceMarines/DevastatorCenturion:Idle#1
entry.value: Taking one suit of armour off.

entry.name: SpaceMarines/DevastatorCenturion:Idle#2
entry.value: Would that our predecessors had these suits during the Heresy.

entry.name: SpaceMarines/DevastatorCenturion:Shaken#0
entry.value: Suit is under fire, but holding.

entry.name: Orks/MegatrakkScrapjet:Idle#0
entry.value: Boss sed I'm grounded! I'll show 'im!

entry.name: Orks/MegatrakkScrapjet:Idle#1
entry.value: Wish I wuz up dere, so I could shoot dahn 'ere

entry.name: Orks/MegatrakkScrapjet:Victory#0
entry.value: ORKS IZ DA BEST, drill it inta dem.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/DevilDog:Attack#2
entry.value: Here come the Devil Dogs! Hoo-yah!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/DevilDog:Hurt#0
entry.value: Keep them away from the promethium tanks!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/DevilDog:Idle#1
entry.value: When do the Hellhounds ship in?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/DevilDog:Idle#2
entry.value: Bane Wolves… those guys scare me.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/DevilDog:Idle#3
entry.value: It's cold when the guns ain't firing.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/DevilDog:Shaken#0
entry.value: Gun the Vulvanor and get us out of range!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/AvengerStrikeFighter:Hurt#0
entry.value: They must have AA behind them.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/AvengerStrikeFighter:Idle#0
entry.value: We have the sun behind us.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/AvengerStrikeFighter:Victory#0
entry.value: Score another one for the naval aces!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/BattleSister:Attack#0
entry.value: In the name of the Emperor.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/BattleSister:Attack#3
entry.value: Suffer not the heretic to live!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/BattleSister:Hurt#0
entry.value: Yea, though their blades cut, I fear nothing.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/BattleSister:Idle#0
entry.value: We are the instruments of Salvation.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/BattleSister:Idle#2
entry.value: We should not rest whilst wickedness works.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/BattleSister:Idle#3
entry.value: So much, so much heresy… so much work.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/BattleSister:AlliedUnit:SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine#0
entry.value: The Saint…? Where she goes, we shall follow!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Canoness:Idle#0
entry.value: Chaos makes work for idle hands.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Canoness:Idle#1
entry.value: We are not without flaw. But we know our sin.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Canoness:Idle#2
entry.value: The holy trinity are my tools… bolter, flamer, melta.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Canoness:Idle#3
entry.value: Redemption is worth any price, my sisters.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Canoness:AlliedUnit:SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine#0
entry.value: I lead but she… she inspires.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Exorcist:Attack#2
entry.value: …oh, Emperor, who art our light and day…

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Exorcist:Attack#3
entry.value: …Hark, the glad sound of our weapons.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Exorcist:Hurt#0
entry.value: …from the depths of woe, I cry to thee…

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Exorcist:Idle#2
entry.value: The Emperor has loosed his swift sword.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Exorcist:Shaken#0
entry.value: Emperor, thy blood and righteousness shall preserve us.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Exorcist:AlliedUnit:SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine#0
entry.value: …behold the wondrous mystery of the Living Saint..!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/CelestianSacresant:Attack#3
entry.value: We shall send you to your rest.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/CelestianSacresant:Broken#0
entry.value: We cannot complete it. We must-

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/CelestianSacresant:Idle#0
entry.value: We travelled the galaxy to end… here.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/CelestianSacresant:Idle#3
entry.value: We are the model to which all aspire.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/CelestianSacresant:AlliedUnit:SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine#0
entry.value: Our namesake, our lady! Our quest is at an end.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/CerastusKnightLancer:Attack#0
entry.value: For the honour of the Questor Mechanicus!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/CerastusKnightLancer:Attack#1
entry.value: We are but a weapon in the right hand of the Emperor.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/CerastusKnightLancer:Idle#3
entry.value: The machine spirits hunger for glory!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/CerastusKnightLancer:Shaken#0
entry.value: What is the glory in this?

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/CerastusKnightLancer:Victory#0
entry.value: They could not withstand my fury.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/CerastusKnightLancer:EnemyUnit:AdeptusMechanicus/KnightCrusader#0
entry.value: A worthy foe! Come, let me close with you.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Dialogus:Attack#0
entry.value: And, yea, the Emperor saw their death and it was good.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Dialogus:Attack#1
entry.value: Rest not my sisters, tell they are no more!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Dialogus:Attack#2
entry.value: Ask not the heretic when a flamer can speak.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Dialogus:Hurt#0
entry.value: What is one more wound to the faithful?

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Dialogus:Idle#1
entry.value: Rest today, for tomorrow we shall be with Him.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Dialogus:Shaken#0
entry.value: Though I walk through death and toil…

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Dialogus:Victory#0
entry.value: Lie down for me, so I might tread higher

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Headquarters:Attack#0
entry.value: Lo, the faithful chorus rings out.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Headquarters:Attack#3
entry.value: You are mistaken if you think us weak.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Headquarters:Victory#0
entry.value: Do not test our walls or our faith.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Headquarters:AlliedUnit:SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine#0
entry.value: O, would that she would visit. Celestine!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Hospitaller:Attack#0
entry.value: My tools hurt as well as they heal.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Hospitaller:Attack#1
entry.value: We hate you, affronts to the faith.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Hospitaller:Attack#2
entry.value: Stand strong in the name of the Emperor.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Hospitaller:Broken#0
entry.value: I must retreat, to preserve the young ones.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Hospitaller:Idle#1
entry.value: Our wounds are testaments to our good work.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Hospitaller:Idle#2
entry.value: Where shall I raise our shrines?

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Hospitaller:Idle#3
entry.value: Hatred is not a sin when the universe is so foul.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Hospitaller:Shaken#0
entry.value: My role is to heal… why am I here?

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Hospitaller:Victory#0
entry.value: My healing touch is somewhat late for that one.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Hospitaller:AlliedUnit:SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine#0
entry.value: My wounds… knit themselves together. How?

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Mortifier:Broken#0
entry.value: Break me more, so I may not know this.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Mortifier:Idle#2
entry.value: I am a sinner, but this-

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Mortifier:Victory#0
entry.value: They are free… for me, there is nothing.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine:Attack#0
entry.value: One day, humanity will be free of this.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine:Attack#2
entry.value: I am the Emperor's tool, to guide as He wills.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine:Hurt#0
entry.value: Death is never the end. Why fear it?

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine:Idle#0
entry.value: Rather darkness than the illumination of the unclean.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine:Idle#1
entry.value: I live in the hearts of the Righteous.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine:Idle#2
entry.value: They would follow me to the Eye of Terror…

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine:Victory#0
entry.value: This is your end, not mine.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/SisterRepentia:Idle#1
entry.value: Cowardice in the face of the enemy.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/SisterRepentia:Idle#3
entry.value: A moment of peace before death.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/SisterRepentia:Victory#0
entry.value: Another step toward redemption or death.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/SisterRepentia:AlliedUnit:SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine#0
entry.value: Celestine was once a Repentia… our beacon of redemption.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Zephyrim:Attack#3
entry.value: Through skies of flame, you are ours.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Zephyrim:Hurt#0
entry.value: Our blood, our wounds, prayers to Him!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Zephyrim:Idle#2
entry.value: Tongues of flame speak prayers too.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Zephyrim:AlliedUnit:SistersOfBattle/SaintCelestine#0
entry.value: Would that we were true angels like her…

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/KataphronBreacher:Hurt#0
entry.value: Functionality Compromised. Machine Extant. Flesh 45%, Declining.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/KataphronBreacher:Idle#2
entry.value: Memory Of Grass, Clouds, Blue Sky… Mind Wipe Error. Erasing.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/RogalDornBattleTank:Idle#2
entry.value: Armageddon, now that was a tank battle…

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/RogalDornBattleTank:Shaken#0
entry.value: They have quite got to One.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/RogalDornBattleTank:Victory#0
entry.value: One is always looking out for new targets.

entry.name: Eldar/DarkReaper:Broken#0
entry.value: It is we who shall be destroyed…

entry.name: Eldar/DarkReaper:Idle#1
entry.value: Destruction is but another path in our long lives.

entry.name: Eldar/DarkReaper:Idle#2
entry.value: Death without fear is our lot.

entry.name: Eldar/DarkReaper:Idle#3
entry.value: The Destroyer took the Smith-God long ago.

entry.name: Eldar/DarkReaper:Shaken#0
entry.value: The Destroyer has turned against us!

entry.name: Necrons/Deathmark:Shaken#0
entry.value: We are precision tools, not targets.

entry.name: Orks/DeffDread:Hurt#0
entry.value: I fink dere's an 'ole in me.

entry.name: Orks/DeffDread:Idle#1
entry.value: Somewun, scratch me schnozz! Drivin' me mad!

entry.name: Orks/DeffDread:Victory#0
entry.value: WAAAGH! Deff Dreads iz da bestest!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Imagifier:Attack#0
entry.value: And Celestine did smite them and saw it was good.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Imagifier:Attack#1
entry.value: And they were the gloried dead!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Imagifier:Attack#2
entry.value: Their holy rage, oh my sisters!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Imagifier:Attack#3
entry.value: Defiant, they stood, against the foe!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Imagifier:Hurt#0
entry.value: Grievious wounds they suffered, but forged on!

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Imagifier:Idle#1
entry.value: In brief moments, they invoked the Emperor's love.

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Imagifier:Idle#2
entry.value: …And Celestine knew her moment was come…

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Imagifier:Idle#3
entry.value: The arch-traitor clutched the fallen angel in a single claw…

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Imagifier:Shaken#0
entry.value: And they sealed the Eternity Gate and were cowed..

entry.name: SistersOfBattle/Imagifier:Victory#0
entry.value: And they returned to holy Terra in triumph!

entry.name: SpaceMarines/Whirlwind:Hurt#0
entry.value: Within small arms range… damage sustained.

entry.name: SpaceMarines/Whirlwind:Idle#2
entry.value: If enemies need softening up, artillery available.

entry.name: SpaceMarines/Whirlwind:Shaken#0
entry.value: This is our Chapter World… how can this be?

entry.name: Tau/RVarnaBattlesuit:Idle#0
entry.value: What are we doing in this fu'llasso?

entry.name: Tau/RVarnaBattlesuit:Idle#1
entry.value: The ho'or-ata-t'chel—the ghost pains—are bad today.

entry.name: Tau/RVarnaBattlesuit:Idle#3
entry.value: How do they make this fio'tak? It's impregnable!

entry.name: Tau/RVarnaBattlesuit:Shaken#0
entry.value: Iur'tae'mont! Where's Farsight when you need him?

entry.name: Drukhari/Archon:Attack#2
entry.value: You are barely worth the killing.

entry.name: Drukhari/Archon:Broken#0
entry.value: Back, back to the city of shadows!

entry.name: Drukhari/Archon:Idle#1
entry.value: Have we killed them all already? Pity.

entry.name: Drukhari/Archon:Idle#2
entry.value: The riches of this world are merely the suffering of its people.

entry.name: Drukhari/Archon:Idle#3
entry.value: How to fill the idle aeons, ahhh…

entry.name: Drukhari/Archon:Shaken#0
entry.value: If this continues, it will take a Haemonculus to wake me…

entry.name: Drukhari/Haemonculus:Attack#3
entry.value: Let me play on their nerves.

entry.name: Drukhari/Haemonculus:Idle#0
entry.value: What sweet suffering to gather next?

entry.name: Drukhari/Haemonculus:Idle#1
entry.value: Do I remember the fall? Do I?

entry.name: Drukhari/Haemonculus:Idle#3
entry.value: Where are my wracks? I require attention!

entry.name: Drukhari/Haemonculus:Shaken#0
entry.value: Oh, they are puissant! I must have them.

entry.name: Drukhari/Headquarters:Attack#0
entry.value: They dare attack our seat of power?

entry.name: Drukhari/Headquarters:Attack#2
entry.value: What madness to assail our walls.

entry.name: Drukhari/Headquarters:Broken#0
entry.value: Archon, save your loy- your subjects!

entry.name: Drukhari/Headquarters:Idle#1
entry.value: The torture gardens are busy tonight.

entry.name: Drukhari/Headquarters:Idle#3
entry.value: The paltry luxuries of this temporary home.

entry.name: Drukhari/Headquarters:Shaken#0
entry.value: Oh, to return to dark Commorragh!

entry.name: Drukhari/Hellion:Idle#1
entry.value: The skies call! The lightning beckons!

entry.name: Drukhari/Incubi:Attack#0
entry.value: We are one with the klaive.

entry.name: Drukhari/Incubi:Attack#2
entry.value: We offer the weak to Khaine.

entry.name: Drukhari/Incubi:Idle#1
entry.value: Our time is bought… it would be a waste not to use us.

entry.name: Drukhari/Incubi:Idle#2
entry.value: There is a purity in hate.

entry.name: Drukhari/Incubi:Idle#3
entry.value: Follow Arha and the Path of Damnation.

entry.name: Drukhari/Incubi:Shaken#0
entry.value: No-one shall walk the Path of Grief for such as we.

entry.name: Drukhari/KabaliteTrueborn:Idle#1
entry.value: Wise, to not squander our precious lives.

entry.name: Drukhari/KabaliteTrueborn:Idle#2
entry.value: We shall spend the millenia in such lassitude…

entry.name: Drukhari/KabaliteTrueborn:Victory#0
entry.value: What did they expect? We are Trueborn.

entry.name: Drukhari/KabaliteWarrior:Broken#0
entry.value: If we flee, the Archon… worse than death.

entry.name: Drukhari/KabaliteWarrior:Idle#0
entry.value: Vatborn we may be, but we are true Drukhari.

entry.name: Drukhari/KabaliteWarrior:Idle#1
entry.value: Bring prisoners, we must practise our aim.

entry.name: Drukhari/KabaliteWarrior:Idle#2
entry.value: Preserve the kabalites, spend the mercenaries.

entry.name: Drukhari/KabaliteWarrior:Victory#0
entry.value: Fools! The Kabal does not send weaklings.

entry.name: Drukhari/Raider:Broken#0
entry.value: Retreat, before they can close with us!

entry.name: Drukhari/Raider:Idle#1
entry.value: Pile the bodies at the rear. Only the weak die.

entry.name: Drukhari/Raider:Idle#3
entry.value: Only Vect recalls the pleasure yachts of ancient days…

entry.name: Drukhari/Raider:Victory#0
entry.value: Put the captives on the trophy-hooks. Alive or dead.

entry.name: Drukhari/RazorwingJetfighter:Hurt#0
entry.value: I did not seek a fair fight!

entry.name: Drukhari/RazorwingJetfighter:Idle#0
entry.value: Better here than the arena death races…

entry.name: Drukhari/RazorwingJetfighter:Idle#2
entry.value: We are the best of the Reavers.

entry.name: Drukhari/RazorwingJetfighter:Idle#3
entry.value: Death from such a distance. The cruelty is that we can't see their torment.

entry.name: Drukhari/RazorwingJetfighter:Victory#0
entry.value: Bisected beautifully. Never saw us coming.

entry.name: Drukhari/Scourge:Attack#0
entry.value: Tread upon the dying, not the dirt.

entry.name: Drukhari/Scourge:Attack#2
entry.value: Do you hear your death upon the wind?

entry.name: Drukhari/Scourge:Hurt#0
entry.value: A brave one who kills a Scourge.

entry.name: Drukhari/Scourge:Idle#2
entry.value: Our wealth is in our wings.

entry.name: Drukhari/Scourge:Idle#3
entry.value: My pinions long to be stretched.

entry.name: Drukhari/Succubus:Attack#2
entry.value: You who are about to die… I salute you.

entry.name: Drukhari/Succubus:Broken#0
entry.value: I will not risk smudging my rouge!

entry.name: Drukhari/Succubus:Idle#1
entry.value: Commorragh is the mob. And I control them.

entry.name: Drukhari/Succubus:Idle#2
entry.value: Tell the Archon I require more sweetmeats.

entry.name: Drukhari/Succubus:Idle#3
entry.value: Ugh, I long to return to civilization, to true suffering.

entry.name: Drukhari/Succubus:Idle#4
entry.value: Shadows and dust. Fear and wonder.

entry.name: Drukhari/Succubus:Shaken#0
entry.value: We Brides of Death do not meet our spouse!

entry.name: Drukhari/Succubus:Victory#0
entry.value: I have… a talent for survival.

entry.name: Drukhari/Tantalus:Attack#1
entry.value: See how the enemies part like waves?

entry.name: Drukhari/Tantalus:Attack#2
entry.value: Tighten the aethersails! Chase them down!

entry.name: Drukhari/Tantalus:Hurt#0
entry.value: The hull is breached! We sink…

entry.name: Drukhari/Tantalus:Idle#1
entry.value: Careful! A scratch and the Archon will…

entry.name: Drukhari/Tantalus:Idle#2
entry.value: A design of the Dark Mirror Kabal. Long gone.

entry.name: Drukhari/Tantalus:Victory#0
entry.value: Consider the fallen, once tall and proud as you.

entry.name: Drukhari/VoidravenBomber:Attack#0
entry.value: Bombs away. Don't look at the darklight!

entry.name: Drukhari/VoidravenBomber:Attack#1
entry.value: Void lance firing. Void mine ready.

entry.name: Drukhari/VoidravenBomber:Idle#1
entry.value: I must compose my next symphony of destruction.

entry.name: Drukhari/VoidravenBomber:Idle#2
entry.value: Silence the engines. Give them the prize of surprise.

entry.name: Drukhari/VoidravenBomber:Idle#3
entry.value: Be careful with the antimatter, you fools!

entry.name: Drukhari/VoidravenBomber:Shaken#0
entry.value: An artist cannot work like this!

entry.name: Drukhari/VoidravenBomber:Victory#0
entry.value: A smoking crater concludes my piece.

entry.name: Drukhari/Wrack:Attack#2
entry.value: Show me- Give me! Your flesh.

entry.name: Drukhari/Wrack:Broken#0
entry.value: Oh, the master will not like this…

entry.name: Drukhari/Wrack:Hurt#0
entry.value: I am no-one. No-one is hurt.

entry.name: Drukhari/Wrack:Idle#0
entry.value: I chose this form… from ennui.

entry.name: Drukhari/Wrack:Idle#1
entry.value: What new hypertoxins. What delightful venoms await?

entry.name: Drukhari/Wrack:Victory#0
entry.value: More subjects for the master's experiments…

entry.name: Drukhari/Wyche:Broken#0
entry.value: I did not train for this.

entry.name: Drukhari/Wyche:Hurt#0
entry.value: We are blooded! But the fight has just begun.

entry.name: Drukhari/Wyche:Shaken#0
entry.value: Do they not appreciate our art?!

entry.name: Drukhari/Wyche:Victory#0
entry.value: Bow and smile for the audience, sisters.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/SydonianDragoon:Idle#2
entry.value: Doubt and death are beyond me.

entry.name: AdeptusMechanicus/SydonianDragoon:Idle#3
entry.value: Endless motion for an eternal empire!

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/FieldOrdnanceBattery:Attack#3
entry.value: We have a firing solution, sir.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/FieldOrdnanceBattery:Idle#0
entry.value: Life in the guard is awfully hard.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/FieldOrdnanceBattery:Idle#2
entry.value: Is this a trench or a depression?

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/FieldOrdnanceBattery:Shaken#0
entry.value: I told you I was ill.

entry.name: AstraMilitarum/FieldOrdnanceBattery:Victory#0
entry.value: Did we-? I think we got 'em!

entry.name: Orks/BurnaBoyz:Hurt#0
entry.value: Oi fell inta ring uv fire!

entry.name: Orks/BurnaBoyz:Idle#2
entry.value: I don't wanna set da world on fire… wait, yes I do.
